1
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:19,390
(Episode 10)

2
00:00:25,310 --> 00:00:26,610
Hey, Jung Rok.

3
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:32,890
It's been a while, but here you are
in front of the elevator again.

4
00:00:33,190 --> 00:00:34,490
Do you think I've been waiting for you?

5
00:00:35,020 --> 00:00:37,240
You're right. I did wait for you.
I waited for about four hours.

6
00:00:39,060 --> 00:00:40,600
What kind of nonsense is that?

7
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:43,150
I'd wait for Yun Seo, but not you.

8
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:48,690
My goodness. Hi, Yun Seo...

9
00:00:50,370 --> 00:00:51,500
Hi, Yoon Sook.

10
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,140
They're a couple working
at the same company.

11
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,570
I saw them secretly holding hands
on the rooftop a couple of times.

12
00:01:19,230 --> 00:01:20,980
I see. No wonder.

13
00:01:22,570 --> 00:01:26,340
Those are the good days.
Showing their affection in secret...

14
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:29,710
and going on short dates on the rooftop.
It must be so fun.

15
00:01:30,510 --> 00:01:33,380
If you're so jealous, you should
also date someone in our firm.

16
00:01:33,380 --> 00:01:37,030
My goodness. Mr. Yeon, aren't you married?

17
00:01:42,490 --> 00:01:44,120
Jung Rok, it's been a while
since I saw you laugh.

18
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:44,930
Yes.

19
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:49,630
It's true that I'm handsome
enough to be married by now.

20
00:01:49,630 --> 00:01:51,640
But unfortunately, I'm still single.

21
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:56,530
In my 30s, I was busy pleading justice...

22
00:01:56,530 --> 00:01:57,720
for the weak.

23
00:01:57,770 --> 00:02:01,240
And in my 40s, I was busy
working day and night...

24
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:04,680
to manage the firm.
That's why I'm still single.

25
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,330
I see.

26
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:10,220
You're really attractive and kind.
You should start dating someone.

27
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,450
You should really date someone in the firm.

28
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,990
Like you mentioned, it'd be so thrilling...

29
00:02:14,990 --> 00:02:16,780
and romantic.

30
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,380
Date someone in the firm?

31
00:02:18,990 --> 00:02:20,040
Who?

32
00:02:22,290 --> 00:02:23,690
Good morning.

33
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:26,100
- Hello.
- Good morning.

34
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,630
- Hi.
- Come and have some waffles.

35
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:29,100
Mr. Choi bought them for us.

36
00:02:29,830 --> 00:02:31,670
That's great. I didn't have breakfast.

37
00:02:31,970 --> 00:02:34,390
They look so delicious. I love waffles.

38
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:36,070
You should sit down and eat.

39
00:02:36,070 --> 00:02:37,090
Take a seat.

40
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:39,600
Goodness.

41
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:44,760
Why did you suddenly get waffles?

42
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:48,050
I just suddenly remembered...

43
00:02:48,050 --> 00:02:50,090
the winter I spent in Canada.

44
00:02:50,220 --> 00:02:52,620
Her heart was frozen like a snowy field,

45
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:56,710
and what could only warm up
my body and soul...

46
00:02:56,730 --> 00:03:00,020
was a plate of waffles
covered in maple syrup.

47
00:03:03,130 --> 00:03:05,850
- How are they?
- They're delicious.

48
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:08,200
- Right?
- Yes.

49
00:03:08,840 --> 00:03:10,370
- The syrup?
- Yes.

50
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,730
It's delicious.

51
00:03:22,290 --> 00:03:24,530
Ms. Oh, what's wrong?

52
00:03:25,220 --> 00:03:26,850
Your eye...

53
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:31,200
Did something get in it?

54
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,160
- Yes.
- Something's in her eye.

55
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,730
- What?
- Bring some saline.

56
00:03:34,730 --> 00:03:36,800
- Something's in it.
- Get out of my way.

57
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,240
I have some in my office.

58
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,440
- Do you want me to check?
- No, it's fine.

59
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,120
You're unbelievable!

60
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:57,150
How could you suddenly wink
at me in front of everyone?

61
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:58,920
In the elevator,

62
00:03:58,990 --> 00:04:01,090
you said that showing
affection in secret...

63
00:04:01,090 --> 00:04:04,160
was both thrilling and romantic.
That's why.

64
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,430
Seriously though.

65
00:04:06,430 --> 00:04:09,080
You can't come at me without any warning.

66
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:11,310
I was surprised, that's all.

67
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:14,190
- Right.
- Gosh.

68
00:04:16,670 --> 00:04:20,140
You know what? I'll make the
most of the time I have left.

69
00:04:20,140 --> 00:04:21,640
I won't let any of it go to waste.

70
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,510
I'll do my best to help you.

71
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:30,570
It's good.

72
00:04:32,420 --> 00:04:35,960
Come to think of it, we haven't
had lunch with Ms. Oh before.

73
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:38,980
That had to be the case...

74
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,040
since restaurants are
usually fully packed...

75
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,040
during lunch.

76
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:45,890
That's right. It's uncomfortable for you.

77
00:04:46,570 --> 00:04:49,040
Was I wrong to ask you to lunch then?

78
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,410
No, it's all right.

79
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:52,930
I'm fine if we can book a room.

80
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:57,780
There aren't many side dishes to eat today.

81
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:59,680
- Let's enjoy though.
- They're still delicious.

82
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,940
Right, dig in.

83
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:12,250
I pushed braised beef
in front of you, Ms. Oh.

84
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,460
I know you're fond of meat.

85
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:15,260
(I know you're fond of meat.)

86
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:19,200
Would you like some water?

87
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,630
Sure. Thank you.

88
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:29,180
I placed the stir-fried ham
in front of you.

89
00:05:29,180 --> 00:05:31,060
I know you have a childish palate.

90
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,710
Right, I immediately ate one.

91
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:35,240
Enjoy your lunch then.

92
00:05:35,450 --> 00:05:37,180
- Mr. Kwon.
- Yes?

93
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:39,840
Who are you texting in the middle of lunch?

94
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,170
A client's been texting me.

95
00:05:44,530 --> 00:05:47,830
Even during meals, you can't let go...

96
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,200
of your passion for this job.

97
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,440
You have become my role model.

98
00:05:51,670 --> 00:05:54,190
I have nothing but respect for you.

99
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,290
Don't you agree?

100
00:05:55,410 --> 00:05:56,660
Yes, I admire you too.

101
00:05:57,110 --> 00:05:58,610
Now you're just kissing his butt.

102
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,770
It's all about the balance.
During meals, you should just eat.

103
00:06:01,780 --> 00:06:03,780
From what I can see, he's a workaholic.

104
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:07,820
I know. Sometimes, I worry
because he works too much.

105
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:10,030
What's wrong if he enjoys it?

106
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:13,120
You truly like your job, don't you?

107
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:17,390
Yes, oh, I truly like to work.

108
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,540
What did you have to say to me?

109
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:36,870
The braised beef earlier.

110
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:38,790
- It was delicious.
- What?

111
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:42,400
Is that what you called me here to say?

112
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:46,320
In TV shows, couples that secretly date...

113
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,860
get together in the stairwell.

114
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:51,070
I've always wanted to do that.

115
00:06:53,430 --> 00:06:56,360
If you're free later, would you
like to join me for dinner?

116
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:58,510
As in a date? I'd love that.

117
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,780
Then I'll book us a nice restaurant.

118
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:02,190
Sure.

119
00:07:19,490 --> 00:07:21,980
Print out the customs
application immediately.

120
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:24,470
Yes, Mr. Kwon. I'll get right on it.

121
00:07:24,530 --> 00:07:26,260
Get on it then. What are you waiting for?

122
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:27,420
Sure.

123
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,640
You were cutting it close.

124
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:33,400
You know very well that
you shouldn't gamble,

125
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,060
but you even went abroad to do so.

126
00:07:36,210 --> 00:07:38,830
This can sound too brutal,

127
00:07:39,010 --> 00:07:41,320
but this isn't your first offense.

128
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:44,740
It won't end with a slap on the wrist.

129
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:50,710
Even I hate the person...

130
00:07:51,090 --> 00:07:52,690
that I've become.

131
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:57,320
I know very well that
what I'm doing is wrong,

132
00:07:58,460 --> 00:08:00,500
but I just can't help myself.

133
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:02,230
You're right.

134
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,990
Why can't you help yourself?

135
00:08:06,970 --> 00:08:08,190
You must be crazy.

136
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:09,860
What?

137
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,180
You think I'm crazy?

138
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:13,690
How could you say such a thing?

139
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:17,710
I wasn't talking about you, sir.

140
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:20,900
I'm sorry.

141
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:39,560
Ms. Kim.

142
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,340
What are you smiling at?

143
00:08:42,070 --> 00:08:44,680
I've been enjoying scuba diving lately...

144
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,140
with friends I met on an app.

145
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:48,110
I'm looking at the photos I took with them.

146
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,150
You met friends on an app?

147
00:08:50,180 --> 00:08:51,200
Yes.

148
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:56,920
On this app, you can meet friends...

149
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,370
who share the same interests.

150
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:02,030
Hold on. Are you interested?

151
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:05,230
I've been distracted lately,

152
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,640
so I'd like to focus
my mind on something else.

153
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,660
Are there people who enjoy the ukulele?
I'd love to join them.

154
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:13,400
Do you even have one?

155
00:09:14,170 --> 00:09:16,110
I have one that I don't use,

156
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:18,060
so you can buy it from me.

157
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:23,570
- Sorry?
- I'll give you a good deal.

158
00:09:24,450 --> 00:09:25,980
I'll bring it to the office soon.

159
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:30,130
No, it's all right.

160
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,290
I need to stop getting tangled up with him.

161
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:49,650
Is it a special day today?

162
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:51,640
This isn't just any restaurant.

163
00:09:53,140 --> 00:09:55,630
You can't go to crowded restaurants,

164
00:09:55,950 --> 00:09:59,210
so we only ate bad food or from the car.

165
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:02,100
I wanted to take you out
to a decent restaurant.

166
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,170
I see.

167
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:08,280
You really surprised me earlier though.

168
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:11,610
As you know, you can be...

169
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:13,390
quite dry.

170
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:16,760
I didn't think you'd ever try anything...

171
00:10:16,770 --> 00:10:18,430
so risky in front of people.

172
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,910
You were bolder than I expected you to be.

173
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:24,060
I didn't know that I had it in me either.

174
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:27,660
I only did it because you like it.

175
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:35,360
Also, it's just like you said.

176
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:38,810
I don't want to waste the
little time we have together.

177
00:10:38,890 --> 00:10:41,060
We only have about a month...

178
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:43,510
to enjoy our secret dating life.

179
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,620
There's nothing there.

180
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,430
When did I eat it all?

181
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:05,040
I truly have a problem with steaks.

182
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:08,320
On an enormous plate,
they give you a small lump of meat.

183
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:11,960
Shouldn't the piece be about half its size?

184
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:15,380
Can't we make a law out of it?

185
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:20,270
That will probably never happen,

186
00:11:22,830 --> 00:11:23,920
so take this instead.

187
00:11:24,570 --> 00:11:26,410
It's not why I mentioned it.

188
00:11:26,770 --> 00:11:29,050
Honestly, it's fine.

189
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,730
I'm good too.

190
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,030
- Then...
- Please stop.

191
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,170
Just have it.

192
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:44,680
Every day has been a joy for me lately.

193
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:48,500
Having you by my side
is the biggest reason.

194
00:11:49,530 --> 00:11:51,910
When I first started off at the law firm,

195
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,650
I told myself to suck it up
and hang in there...

196
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:57,560
for three months.

197
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:01,120
But I'm enjoying my work now,

198
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,970
and I even like the company dinners.

199
00:12:03,710 --> 00:12:05,380
The workshop was fun too.

200
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:07,420
Everything about it is fun and exciting.

201
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,150
Mr. Yeon was right.

202
00:12:09,150 --> 00:12:10,940
You're like Princess Ann
in "Roman Holiday".

203
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,380
You leave your frustrating life...

204
00:12:13,380 --> 00:12:15,430
and find joy in what others view as normal.

205
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:19,210
Have you watched "Roman Holiday"?

206
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:23,590
I think I saw it on TV
when it was aired as a classic.

207
00:12:23,590 --> 00:12:25,030
Are you kidding me?

208
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:27,680
"Roman Holiday" should be watched properly.

209
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:29,740
It's my favorite movie.

210
00:12:31,670 --> 00:12:35,210
I have the DVD at home.
Would you like to watch it together?

211
00:12:35,340 --> 00:12:38,440
It's Saturday tomorrow.
You should come to my house.

212
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:40,160
Sure.

213
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:41,730
Wait a second.

214
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:43,230
What did I just say?

215
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:44,300
Wait a second.

216
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:47,840
Does that mean I'll go over
to Ms. Oh's house tomorrow?

217
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:49,070
Oh my goodness.

218
00:12:49,220 --> 00:12:51,910
I really just wanted to
watch a movie with him.

219
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:54,810
She asked me to come over to
watch a movie, so I said yes.

220
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:56,420
