00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:47,390
Hello, it's Jung Rok.

262
00:15:47,930 --> 00:15:49,020
Oh, right.

263
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:15,310
Well, then... Come on in.

264
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:16,350
Okay.

265
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:43,530
Oh, right. This is for you.

266
00:16:43,790 --> 00:16:46,060
- What is it?
- It's a gift.

267
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,760
You said you have insomnia.

268
00:16:49,160 --> 00:16:52,020
I heard a glass of wine is
helpful for getting good sleep.

269
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,320
Thank you.

270
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,650
I'm looking forward to tonight...

271
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:59,080
What did you just say?

272
00:16:59,340 --> 00:17:00,740
You look forward to tonight?

273
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:03,160
I meant, I'm looking forward to
getting a good night's sleep.

274
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:05,520
What if he misunderstood me?

275
00:17:08,410 --> 00:17:10,650
Right. I hope you get a
good night's sleep tonight.

276
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:13,480
Can I take it off?

277
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:15,320
Why did you leave out the object?

278
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,730
I meant, "Can I take off my jacket"?

279
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:21,270
You're an attorney. How could you
be so horrible at grammar?

280
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:24,640
What if she takes it the wrong way?

281
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:27,700
I meant my jacket. This jacket.

282
00:17:27,930 --> 00:17:29,810
- Yes, sure.
- Okay.

283
00:17:35,170 --> 00:17:36,870
Can I put this here?

284
00:17:37,010 --> 00:17:38,030
Okay.

285
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:47,220
You have a lovely home.

286
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:50,100
Do you want to take a look around?

287
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:52,250
- Shall we?
- Okay.

288
00:17:56,290 --> 00:17:57,920
This is the study.

289
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:03,400
This is the space I spend most
of my time in at my house.

290
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:08,080
You have so many books.

291
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:10,280
Yes, I really enjoy reading.

292
00:18:15,810 --> 00:18:17,440
Someone might think...

293
00:18:17,550 --> 00:18:20,880
this dust piled up because I never
read a book, but that's not true.

294
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:23,260
I read a lot, but I don't clean often.

295
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:26,650
I clean a lot, but I don't read...

296
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:29,380
No...

297
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,860
Why don't we take a look
around somewhere else?

298
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,700
- This is my bedroom.
- I see.

299
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:46,210
Isn't the dressing table gorgeous?

300
00:18:47,380 --> 00:18:49,350
I really love this bed too.

301
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:52,380
This type of design seems ordinary,
but it's very rare.

302
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:54,520
The headboard is set just right,

303
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:56,360
and the mattress is really bouncy too.

304
00:18:57,250 --> 00:19:00,380
Hold on. Why am I explaining
my bed in detail to him right now?

305
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:03,410
What do you mean by saying the
mattress is really bouncy?

306
00:19:03,730 --> 00:19:05,700
Are you asking him to lie
down next to you or what?

307
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:09,150
I hope he doesn't interpret it like that.

308
00:19:14,540 --> 00:19:16,040
Wait. Why did you turn off the lights?

309
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:18,560
Turning off the lights in the bedroom?
Get a grip, Jung Rok.

310
00:19:20,610 --> 00:19:21,630
It was a mistake.

311
00:19:23,380 --> 00:19:25,110
Of course, I know.

312
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:30,060
Then shall we go see the kitchen?

313
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:40,970
I'll send you a written opinion via email.

314
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,110
If you have an opinion,
please send a reply.

315
00:19:43,630 --> 00:19:44,650
Okay.

316
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,410
- Ms. Dan.
- Mr. Choi.

317
00:19:49,770 --> 00:19:51,540
What brings you here on the weekend?

318
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:53,420
I had some work left regarding a case.

319
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:54,730
What about you?

320
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,550
I had some work left too.

321
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:03,470
I'm glad. I brought a ukulele
I wanted to give you.

322
00:20:03,620 --> 00:20:06,270
I'll bring it to your office later on.

323
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:17,650
What on earth? Just the two of us
in the office on the weekend?

324
00:20:17,670 --> 00:20:18,760
Is this what they call...

325
00:20:20,540 --> 00:20:21,560
fate?

326
00:20:22,970 --> 00:20:24,540
Fate, my foot.

327
00:20:24,770 --> 00:20:26,110
Snap back into it, Moon Hee.

328
00:20:26,380 --> 00:20:27,660
You promised yourself not to be tempted.

329
00:20:40,390 --> 00:20:43,080
Ms. Dan, I brought the ukulele for you.

330
00:20:44,590 --> 00:20:47,490
- Oh, how much is it?
- It's fine.

331
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:49,550
Just buy me a drink sometime.

332
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,900
- A drink?
- Yes.

333
00:20:53,340 --> 00:20:55,310
Okay, then. Here you go.

334
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,040
Thank you for everything.

335
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:02,500
You were a part of me,

336
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,400
and I was a part of you.

337
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:08,300
You and I became one and made...

338
00:21:09,050 --> 00:21:10,480
all those emotional harmonies.

339
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,140
I'll never forget it.

340
00:21:17,130 --> 00:21:19,240
As a farewell, I will play this song...

341
00:21:19,630 --> 00:21:20,990
that we used to enjoy.

342
00:22:05,010 --> 00:22:06,470
This is the end of my farewell song.

343
00:22:08,610 --> 00:22:10,040
Well then, here you go.

344
00:22:10,550 --> 00:22:11,630
Thank you.

345
00:22:12,150 --> 00:22:13,440
Handle it with great care.

346
00:22:16,620 --> 00:22:18,660
Do you know how to play the ukulele?

347
00:22:18,660 --> 00:22:22,060
I learned briefly a long time ago.

348
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:25,140
I know how to play basic chords.

349
00:22:28,730 --> 00:22:30,570
C chord.

350
00:22:31,940 --> 00:22:34,320
F... F chord...

351
00:22:35,370 --> 00:22:37,200
Your posture is all wrong.

352
00:22:39,710 --> 00:22:40,730
Here.

353
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:43,030
Let's see.

354
00:22:43,810 --> 00:22:45,480
Loosen your shoulders.

355
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:50,920
Then you must hold the
ukulele very preciously...

356
00:22:51,190 --> 00:22:52,690
like it's a little baby.

357
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,210
Just like this.

358
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:14,340
The feelings I started developing for him

359
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:21,280
I wished that those
feelings wouldn't be love

360
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:28,390
And the pitiful look in your eyes
when you looked at me

361
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:34,310
I wished that I was just mistaken

362
00:23:37,300 --> 00:23:41,380
Our love was only blessed by the skies

363
00:23:42,510 --> 00:23:44,810
And no one else

364
00:23:45,310 --> 00:23:47,010
Please!

365
00:23:48,340 --> 00:23:50,320
Let my love come true!

366
00:23:52,250 --> 00:23:55,820
I just want to love him!

367
00:23:56,390 --> 00:23:58,490
Mr. Choi!

368
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:05,540
You must watch a lot of movies at home.

369
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:09,530
Yes, I really like watching movies.

370
00:24:09,530 --> 00:24:10,550
I see.

371
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,470
- Just a second.
- Okay.

372
00:24:17,170 --> 00:24:18,190
Yes, Prosecutor.

373
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:20,530
Yes.

374
00:24:21,540 --> 00:24:23,900
No, next Wednesday isn't a good day for me.

375
00:24:24,810 --> 00:24:26,070
No, that's not it.

376
00:24:36,130 --> 00:24:37,720
Where did it go? I'm sure it was here.

377
00:24:48,340 --> 00:24:50,010
Hey, Hyuk Joon.

378
00:24:50,010 --> 00:24:52,530
I can't find the Blu-ray player.
Where did it go?

379
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,710
What? You took it to get it repaired?

380
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:58,570
You should've told me before you took it.

381
00:24:58,650 --> 00:25:01,180
What? Every time anything
broke in your house,

382
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:02,820
I always took it to get it repaired.

383
00:25:02,890 --> 00:25:04,450
Why are you being so sensitive
about it all of a sudden?

384
00:25:04,650 --> 00:25:06,450
My goodness.

385
00:25:07,660 --> 00:25:08,750
Okay, bye.

386
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:13,160
Are we going to start watching the movie?

387
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,420
Well...

388
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:20,940
- I can't play it.
- What do you mean?

389
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:24,800
Is it because you're worried
that it might not be fun?

390
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:27,940
It's okay. I don't normally
enjoy watching movies,

391
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:31,260
but since it's your favorite movie,
I'm open to watching it.

392
00:25:32,450 --> 00:25:34,050
No, that's not it.

393
00:25:34,920 --> 00:25:37,120
I meant I don't have the Blu-ray player...

394
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:38,790
to play the movie.

395
00:25:44,190 --> 00:25:46,580
It's getting repaired right now.
I must've forgotten about it.

396
00:25:47,460 --> 00:25:48,520
I see.

397
00:25:56,270 --> 00:25:58,450
We'll just have to make do...

398
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:07,480
We'll just have to make do with a laptop.

399
00:26:07,780 --> 00:26:09,290
I'll quickly download the movie.

400
00:26:09,290 --> 00:26:11,360
I'm fine with that. You can take your time.

401
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:15,140
Go ahead.

402
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,320
I've been wanting to see your trophies.

403
00:26:23,330 --> 00:26:24,860
Is it okay if I go take a close look?

404
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:26,390
Sure.

405
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,580
KBC Popularity Award.

406
00:26:34,610 --> 00:26:36,710
MBU Hot Issue Celebrity Award.

407
00:26:36,710 --> 00:26:38,350
TBM Teen Choice Award.

408
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:39,880
SBC Netizens' Award.

409
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:43,140
Gosh, you received so many awards.

410
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,590
Yes, I did.

411
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:48,000
The problem is that they're
all popularity awards.

412
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:50,790
Why is that a problem?

413
00:26:56,130 --> 00:26:59,540
I never got an award for acting.
They're all popularity awards,

414
00:26:59,540 --> 00:27:00,660
so it's a little embarrassing.

415
00:27:00,970 --> 00:27:02,440
Why is that embarrassing?

416
00:27:03,470 --> 00:27:06,670
The fact that you're popular
means a lot of people like you.

417
00:27:06,810 --> 00:27:10,550
I personally think it's very
hard to make people like you.

418
00:27:11,310 --> 00:27:12,600
I'm very impressed.

419
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:14,770
Really?

420
00:27:16,350 --> 00:27:19,070
But if I get another chance to act,

421
00:27:19,090 --> 00:27:21,360
I feel like I'll be able
to do a really good job.

422
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:25,260
Back then, I didn't really know
how it felt to like someone...

423
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:28,160
or how it felt to have my heart flutter.

424
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,860
So I didn't really know how
to express those feelings.

425
00:27:30,230 --> 00:27:31,320
But now...

426
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:36,810
Now, I think I kind of know.

427
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:51,900
Which drama is that photo from?

428
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:53,240
You look really pretty.

429
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:56,400
This photo isn't from a drama.

430
00:27:56,860 --> 00:27:59,450
This chocolate bar advertisement
is how I made my debut.

431
00:27:59,960 --> 00:28:02,580
All the chocolate bars got sold out
because of this advertisement,

432
00:28:03,170 --> 00:28:06,400
and people even started
calling me "the chocolate fairy".

433
00:28:06,770 --> 00:28:09,800
- You didn't see this advertisement?
- No.

434
00:28:09,870 --> 00:28:13,480
My goodness, we shouldn't
watch "Roman Holiday".

435
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:14,930
Come here.

436
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:16,910
- Hurry. Hurry.
- Okay.

437
00:28:24,290 --> 00:28:28,030
♫ <i>I love everything,
even the sorrow of this world</i> ♫

438
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:31,010
Look at this. Don't I look
really pretty and cute?

439
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:37,660
I look pretty here as well, don't I?
I also look very innocent and pure.

440
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,170
How pretty.

441
00:28:42,170 --> 00:28:43,840
Don't I look really elegant?

442
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:47,540
Do you also want to see
my photoshoot collection?

443
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:50,650
- That? Sure.
- Would you like to see?

444
00:29:00,190 --> 00:29:03,520
Back then I didn't know,
but I really was pretty.

445
00:29:04,490 --> 00:29:05,520
Don't you agree?

446
00:29:08,260 --> 00:29:10,920
Come to think of it,
why aren't you responding?

447
00:29:12,540 --> 00:29:14,780
- Don't I look pretty?
- You do look pretty.

448
00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:17,580
But you look even prettier now.

449
00:29:18,540 --> 00:29:20,310
Right now, sitting in front of me.

450
00:29:28,120 --> 00:29:30,390
Can I have this?

451
00:29:30,850 --> 00:29:32,070
- This?
- Yes.

452
00:29:32,590 --> 00:29:35,650
To be honest, I want all of them,
but that doesn't sound right.

453
00:29:35,990 --> 00:29:38,410
But I really want to take this one.

454
00:29:39,900 --> 00:29:41,800
Sure, go ahead.

455
00:29:42,670 --> 00:29:44,630
You know what? I'll give you one more.

456
00:29:44,630 --> 00:29:47,000
- Okay.
- There are a lot of nice ones,

457
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,770
so you must choose carefully.

458
00:29:50,210 --> 00:29:52,110
- Is this from that advertisement?
- Yes.

459
00:30:05,090 --> 00:30:06,240
I like the smell.

460
00:30:06,460 --> 00:30:07,740
I'm glad you like it.

461
00:30:12,300 --> 00:30:13,630
I feel so bad.

462
00:30:14,160 --> 00:30:15,830
I invited you over so
we could watch a movie,

463
00:30:15,970 --> 00:30:17,730
but we didn't get to watch anything.

464
00:30:18,730 --> 00:30:19,790
I'm sorry.

465
00:30:19,940 --> 00:30:22,790
I'm actually relieved that we
didn't get to watch a movie.

466
00:30:23,870 --> 00:30:24,890
What?

467
00:30:27,410 --> 00:30:29,290
To be honest, I couldn't sleep a wink...

468
00:30:30,150 --> 00:30:31,580
last night.

469
00:30:32,980 --> 00:30:34,070
I got really nervous.

470
00:30:34,980 --> 00:30:38,520
The thought of coming to
your house made me feel unfamiliar,

471
00:30:38,990 --> 00:30:40,240
awkward,

472
00:30:41,390 --> 00:30:42,650
and excited at the same time.

473
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,130
I felt the same way.

474
00:30:47,630 --> 00:30:50,420
The thought of having you
over at my house...

475
00:30:50,830 --> 00:30:52,470
made my heart flutter so much.

476
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:55,550
I already have trouble sleeping
because of insomnia.

477
00:30:56,010 --> 00:30:58,660
But last night, I literally
stayed up all night.

478
00:31:01,380 --> 00:31:03,080
I thought I was the only
one who felt that way.

479
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:05,080
I also felt the same way.

480
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:08,520
Anyway, I was really nervous.
But I feel a lot better...

481
00:31:08,520 --> 00:31:11,140
after having chatted with
you a lot as we looked...

482
00:31:11,220 --> 00:31:12,490
at your photoshoot collection.

483
00:31:12,490 --> 00:31:13,990
Me too.

484
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:18,740
I also loosened up as we
started looking at my photos.

485
00:31:19,760 --> 00:31:22,800
Before that, I couldn't stop
thinking about the fact...

486
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,870
that you and I were at
my place all by ourselves.

487
00:31:24,870 --> 00:31:27,290
And that made me imagine so many things.

488
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:35,400
But that doesn't necessarily mean...

489
00:31:35,510 --> 00:31:37,650
that I imagined anything bad.

490
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:42,180
By bad, do you mean...

491
00:31:43,650 --> 00:31:45,660
Well...

492
00:31:52,360 --> 00:31:53,830
Something like this?

493
00:31:57,170 --> 00:31:58,220
Or...

494
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:01,060
this?

495
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:30,590
Hey, Hyuk Joon.

496
00:32:31,870 --> 00:32:34,110
What? You're going to be late? How late?

497
00:32:34,940 --> 00:32:37,420
Oh, okay. Call me when you get here.

498
00:32:37,940 --> 00:32:39,030
Okay, bye.

499
00:32:46,980 --> 00:32:49,230
I had fun with Mr. Kwon last night.

500
00:32:52,620 --> 00:32:54,760
Is this why people get married?

501
00:32:56,130 --> 00:32:58,580
Being with that person is just fun...

502
00:32:59,230 --> 00:33:00,830
no matter what you do.

503
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:04,830
Lee Gang Joon, the former director...

504
00:33:04,830 --> 00:33:07,800
of Jeguk Entertainment who was
arrested on drug charges,

505
00:33:07,870 --> 00:33:11,140
returns as vice president
of Jeguk Holdings,

506
00:33:11,140 --> 00:33:12,870
the holding company of Jeguk Group.

507
00:33:12,980 --> 00:33:16,150
The entire group will be reorganized...

508
00:33:16,150 --> 00:33:18,700
as he will supervise various subsidiaries.

509
00:33:18,810 --> 00:33:21,220
Some are criticizing that...

510
00:33:21,220 --> 00:33:23,260
his comeback is premature.

511
00:33:23,490 --> 00:33:25,020
Vice President Lee Gang Joon
of Jeguk Group.

512
00:33:25,020 --> 00:33:28,020
He was famously involved in a
drug case with an actress.

513
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,470
- Was it Oh Yun Seo?
- Oh Yun Seo?

514
00:33:30,530 --> 00:33:33,930
He stalked Oh Yun Seo, but she
wouldn't accept his advances.

515
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:36,980
So he called narcotics to
frame her on drug charges.

516
00:33:37,730 --> 00:33:39,840
At the time, Jeguk Group promised...

517
00:33:39,840 --> 00:33:43,380
to take all criticism heavily
and Vice President Lee...

518
00:33:44,210 --> 00:33:45,600
Are you off to work?

519
00:33:47,380 --> 00:33:48,940
Where else would I go at this hour?

520
00:33:49,110 --> 00:33:50,200
See you.

521
00:33:51,010 --> 00:33:52,130
Hold on.

522
00:33:53,850 --> 00:33:55,720
Is anything up with Ms. Oh?

523
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,760
I'm just curious, that's all.

